Alice Goodman , American poet , was educated at Harvard University and Cambridge where she studied English and American literature . She has written the libretti for two of the operas of John Adams , Nixon in China and The Death of Klinghoffer . Although she was raised as a Reform Jew in Minnesota , she is currently an ordained Anglican priest serving in England . Goodman resumed writing with John Adams on the opera Doctor Atomic , however she withdrew from this project after a year . It is reported that she is now working with Peter Sellars on a version of The Consolation of Philosophy . She is married to the noted British poet Geoffrey Hill . In 2006 , Alice Goodman took up the post of chaplain at Trinity College , Cambridge . 